    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Labrum of female Dialictus; (A) nest-building species, (B) parasitic species. Arrows indicate apical process." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10094485/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10094487>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Mandible of female Dialictus with subapical tooth (A) present, (B) absent, as indicated by arrow." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10094487/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10094489>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Gena of female Dialictus (A) narrower than eye, (B) wider than eye." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10094489/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10094491>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Dorsolateral angle of pronotum (A) obtuse, (B) acute." ;
